1
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,125
We should go out again soon.

2
00:00:14,208 --> 00:00:15,375
Yeah, for sure!

3
00:00:15,458 --> 00:00:16,791
Next time, let's go
to the coast!

4
00:00:16,875 --> 00:00:18,375
I love the ocean.

5
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,625
[gasps] Yo!

6
00:00:27,708 --> 00:00:29,333
[MIKASA, SARA]
Hm?

7
00:00:29,416 --> 00:00:30,541
Hey.

8
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:32,958
Huh? Yeah?

9
00:00:33,041 --> 00:00:34,083
You okay?

10
00:00:34,166 --> 00:00:36,000
Sure! Why d'you ask?

11
00:00:36,083 --> 00:00:37,541
[MIKASA]
I don't know, you just seem...

12
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:40,875
[YUU panting]

13
00:00:40,958 --> 00:00:42,083
I actually made it.

14
00:00:42,166 --> 00:00:43,333
[NACHI]
You little punk!

15
00:00:43,416 --> 00:00:45,958
I see you, just barely
sliding in here in time!

16
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:46,958
Must have been another...

17
00:00:47,041 --> 00:00:48,500
Would you give it
a rest, already?

18
00:00:48,583 --> 00:00:49,791
You'll end up hurting him.

19
00:00:49,875 --> 00:00:51,166
[NACHI] Did you have
a good time with her?

20
00:00:51,250 --> 00:00:52,625
[YUU]
Of course. C'mon, cut it out!

21
00:00:52,708 --> 00:00:54,083
[NACHI]
Yeah, I bet you did!

22
00:00:54,166 --> 00:00:56,166
Haruna the ladykillah!

23
00:00:57,416 --> 00:01:02,375
♪

24
00:01:13,666 --> 00:01:14,958
<i>The place that I always dreamed</i>

25
00:01:15,041 --> 00:01:17,916
<i>I'd reach one day</i>
<i>is too high above us</i>

26
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,000
<i>To get to</i>

27
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:21,166
<i>The promise we made is fading</i>

28
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:24,291
<i>every moment we</i>
<i>conform like they do</i>

29
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:25,666
<i>I wanna move on my own</i>

30
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:27,041
<i>Step away from the crowd</i>

31
00:01:27,125 --> 00:01:28,500
<i>I wanna dance to my own beat</i>

32
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:30,875
<i>I'm done trying to blend in</i>

33
00:01:32,083 --> 00:01:34,666
<i>I won't be tied</i>
<i>to a tedious world</i>

34
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:37,500
<i>Repeating each day like</i>
<i>a broken record sickens me</i>

35
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:40,041
<i>(No matter how I try</i>
<i>I can't escape repetition)</i>

36
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:41,166
<i>It's hard to change it up</i>

37
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:42,750
<i>When no one else is listening</i>

38
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:44,541
<i>We're in a box, stuck in a box</i>

39
00:01:44,625 --> 00:01:47,083
<i>Meant to stifle what we feel</i>

40
00:01:47,166 --> 00:01:49,833
<i>Forced to erase all</i>
<i>that we know is real</i>

41
00:01:49,916 --> 00:01:51,125
<i>But I refuse to be locked up</i>

42
00:01:51,208 --> 00:01:52,208
<i>Won't live in this prison</i>

43
00:01:52,291 --> 00:01:54,125
<i>Gotta fight for open skies</i>

44
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:56,916
<i>Time to break free</i>

45
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,875
<i>Open our hearts to a world and</i>
<i>go racing forward to the light</i>

46
00:02:00,958 --> 00:02:02,583
<i>These broken chains</i>
<i>can't hold us back</i>

47
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:06,583
<i>We're finally on track to heal</i>
<i>all the fractures in ourselves</i>

48
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:07,958
<i>As we climb and ascend</i>

49
00:02:08,041 --> 00:02:09,291
<i>Aiming high to the end</i>

50
00:02:09,375 --> 00:02:11,750
<i>We'll feel a climber's high</i>

51
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:14,583
<i>Hear these words and know your</i>
<i>dream can be stronger than steel</i>

52
00:02:14,666 --> 00:02:15,791
<i>Just believe</i>

53
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:16,583
<i>You have the power</i>

54
00:02:16,666 --> 00:02:20,208
<i>Let your voice be heard</i>

55
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:25,250
♪

56
00:02:29,708 --> 00:02:32,166
Hey, Fuuka. I almost
hate to ask you this,

57
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:34,000
but how are those
lyrics coming along?

58
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:36,750
Uh... yeah, about that.

59
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:39,708
I'm just gonna need
a little more time.

60
00:02:39,791 --> 00:02:40,708
No prob.

61
00:02:40,791 --> 00:02:41,958
But we're counting on you!

62
00:02:42,041 --> 00:02:43,333
Come on, Nachi.

63
00:02:43,416 --> 00:02:45,166
You know that's not helpful
to her right now, man.

64
00:02:45,250 --> 00:02:47,541
What do you mean?
I was being encouraging.

65
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:49,541
How? By putting more
pressure on her?

66
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:51,583
[NACHI] Ugh. Fine,
I hear you, I'm sorry.

67
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:54,125
Just get it done ASAP, okay?

68
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:55,666
Are you serious right now?

69
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:57,125
You just did it to her again.

70
00:02:57,208 --> 00:02:58,291
What did I do?

71
00:02:58,375 --> 00:03:00,041
There is nothing wrong
with what I said!

72
00:03:00,125 --> 00:03:01,875
You really are
clueless, aren't you?

73
00:03:01,958 --> 00:03:02,708
[NACHI]
Wait, about what?

74
00:03:02,791 --> 00:03:03,708
Are you okay?

75
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:06,250
[FUUKA gasps]
I'm good.

76
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:07,750
I hope you know
I'm happy to help

77
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,541
if there's ever anything
I can do for you.

78
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,375
[FUUKA gasps]

79
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:11,833
For whatever that's worth.

80
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:13,958
I mean, it's not like I've
ever written lyrics before!

81
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:16,166
I might end up being more of a
hindrance than a help, really--

82
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:17,666
Just go away!

83
00:03:17,750 --> 00:03:18,708
[YUU]
Uh--

84
00:03:20,541 --> 00:03:24,791
I mean... I just don't do
so great when I'm rushed!

85
00:03:32,041 --> 00:03:37,125
[KOYUKI] ♪ I don't regret
one day with you ♪

86
00:03:37,208 --> 00:03:38,375
It's so crazy.

87
00:03:38,458 --> 00:03:39,958
I can't believe
our stupid brother

88
00:03:40,041 --> 00:03:41,958
is the boyfriend of
a huge star like her.

89
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:44,708
One rare instance of
childhood crushes working out.

90
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,791
'Course, they're crazy,
so we'll see.

91
00:03:46,875 --> 00:03:48,708
Come on, don't talk
about them like that.

92
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:50,750
I'm sure Koyuki knows
what she's doing.

93
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,500
Between his band
and his girlfriend,

94
00:03:52,583 --> 00:03:54,333
Yuu is living the teenage dream!

95
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:57,375
He certainly is and
I'm so happy for him.

96
00:03:57,458 --> 00:03:58,625
He's changed a lot.

97
00:03:58,708 --> 00:04:00,166
Yeah, He's growing up.

98
00:04:05,625 --> 00:04:06,916
[sighs]

99
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:10,166
Just go away!

100
00:04:19,083 --> 00:04:23,583
[phone line ringing]

101
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:25,166
Hey, Akitsuki?

102
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,041
Oh! Yuu! Hey.

103
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:28,166
[YUU]
Hi.

104
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,625
You need something?

105
00:04:29,708 --> 00:04:32,333
[YUU]
Oh, well, no, not exactly.

106
00:04:32,416 --> 00:04:34,958
I wanted to talk to you
about the lyrics though.

107
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:36,958
Oh, yeah? What about them?

108
00:04:37,041 --> 00:04:38,916
[YUU] I was just thinking
that I might've been

109
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:43,125
a little insensitive, and I was
worried that I made you angry.

110
00:04:43,208 --> 00:04:45,208
Are you? Angry?

111
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:47,916
No, not really.

112
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,583
[YUU] Well, don't push
yourself too hard.

113
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:53,875
Wow, I keep saying
that, don't I? Sorry.

114
00:04:53,958 --> 00:04:55,541
You don't have to apologize.

115
00:04:55,625 --> 00:04:58,000
[YUU]
Sorry. Crap, I did it again.

116
00:04:58,083 --> 00:05:01,375
Well, I don't want to keep you,
so see you tomorrow.

117
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:02,416
Bye.

118
00:05:06,875 --> 00:05:08,750
[FUUKA]
Please stop being so nice.

119
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,458
It doesn't help.

120
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:30,583
--[phone buzzes]
--[YUU] Uh--

121
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:34,166
Tama?

122
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:37,833
[YUU]
Hey! You still working?

123
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:40,208
I am. We've been
filming a lot today.

124
00:05:40,291 --> 00:05:41,541
[YUU]
That sounds intense.

125
00:05:41,625 --> 00:05:43,500
[KOYUKI]
Mm-hmm! But guess what?

126
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:47,041
I think I'm gonna be able to
see your band's gig after all!

127
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:48,166
Oh, that's great!

128
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:50,625
I guess I'd better
not suck, then, huh?

129
00:05:50,708 --> 00:05:52,083
[KOYUKI]
As if you could!

130
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,166
So, how're things?
How's the new song?

131
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:57,708
Well, actually, the lyrics
haven't been finished quite yet.

132
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:59,166
That's not good.

133
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:00,541
[YUU]
Tell me this.

134
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:02,500
How do you come up
with your lyrics, Tama?

135
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:03,875
[KOYUKI]
Huh?

136
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:06,791
Seems Akitsuki's having
a bit of trouble with them.

137
00:06:06,875 --> 00:06:08,958
[KOYUKI] Well, everyone's
approach is different.

138
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:10,291
It's instinctive.

139
00:06:10,375 --> 00:06:13,250
So, I don't know how
much I could help her.

140
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:14,541
Oh, gotcha.

141
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,541
I've never written a
song before in my life.

142
00:06:16,625 --> 00:06:18,666
I just feel bad I
can't help her out.

143
00:06:18,750 --> 00:06:21,125
So, I thought maybe
hearing what works for you

144
00:06:21,208 --> 00:06:22,250
might give her some ideas.

145
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:24,333
[KOYUKI]
All of my songs...

146
00:06:24,416 --> 00:06:27,208
...have been written with
the person I love in mind.

147
00:06:27,291 --> 00:06:29,000
[gasps]

148
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:30,750
[KOYUKI]
Fuuka already told me.

149
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,041
She doesn't have anyone
that she loves.

150
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:36,291
So, hearing about my process
isn't going to help her.

151
00:06:37,875 --> 00:06:39,166
[YUU]
I see.

152
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:40,458
Sorry about that.

153
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:42,916
Wish I had some
useful advice for you.

154
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,166
[YUU]
It's cool.

155
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,208
[KOYUKI]
Talk to you later, okay?

156
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:52,416
[KOYUKI sighs]

157
00:06:54,208 --> 00:06:55,750
This has to stop.

158
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:57,541
I can't stand it.

159
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:08,250
It's one-sided, but, yes.

160
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,625
I guess I write songs
as a way to express it.

161
00:07:10,708 --> 00:07:13,750
I've never actually
told him how I feel.

162
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:18,583
[FUUKA] I didn't understand her
at all then, but I get it now.

163
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,666
[FUUKA]
What's happened to me?

164
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:24,125
I wish I'd never realized it.

165
00:07:30,416 --> 00:07:32,333
[FUUKA]
I mean, after all,

166
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:35,083
I hadn't even thought
about it before.

167
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:52,250
[music playing]

168
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,208
[FUUKA]
It's undeniable.

169
00:07:57,291 --> 00:08:00,958
I know in my heart what
this feeling is. I do.

170
00:08:02,583 --> 00:08:06,000
[FUUKA] I am completely
in love with Yuu.

171
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,250
[YUU]
Akitsuki!

172
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,916
[FUUKA gasps]

173
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:14,333
Is something wrong?

174
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:15,583
[FUUKA]
Mm-mm.

175
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:20,958
Wanna have your mind blown?

176
00:08:21,041 --> 00:08:23,166
What? You finished it?

177
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:24,416
[FUUKA]
Mm-hmm!

178
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:34,166
[music playing]

179
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:45,541
[gasps] This is amazing!

180
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:46,375
Why thank you!

181
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:47,875
[door opens]

182
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:50,041
[NACHI]
Yep, figured you'd be up here.

183
00:08:50,125 --> 00:08:52,208
Wait, did you finish the lyrics?

184
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:53,833
[FUUKA]
Mm-hmm!

185
00:08:53,916 --> 00:08:55,458
[NACHI]
Come on, share! I wanna hear it!

186
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:57,000
[NACHI yelps]
God, that hurt!

187
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:58,333
Why would you--

188
00:08:58,416 --> 00:08:59,458
--[NACHI groaning]
--Hands to yourself, little boy.

189
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:00,958
Wait your turn.

190
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:03,500
Hey, let's go play it now!

191
00:09:03,583 --> 00:09:04,666
Sure!

192
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:11,166
[FUUKA] Don't smile
at me, not like that.

193
00:09:23,083 --> 00:09:26,833
[FUUKA] I believe...
it'll be our best show ever.

194
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:30,416
[FUUKA sighs]

195
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:35,625
[HIBIKI] We're coming
to hear you play, so,

196
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:36,916
don't screw up, okay?

197
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,166
No one said you had to come.

198
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,375
Oh, stop.

199
00:09:39,458 --> 00:09:40,791
We couldn't miss our
brother's big moment!

200
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:43,250
One question:
Will Koyuki be there?

201
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:45,000
[YUU]
Uh--I'm not sure?

202
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,166
So, that's a yes, then.

203
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:47,125
He's bad at this.

204
00:09:47,208 --> 00:09:48,208
[MAYA]
Stop, you two.

205
00:09:48,291 --> 00:09:49,541
Give him a break today.

206
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:51,041
[YUU sighs]
I'm heading out!

207
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:53,666
Go get 'em, Yuu!

208
00:09:56,083 --> 00:09:57,291
[NACHI'S GRANDMA]
Wait just a second!

209
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,750
[gasps] What is it, Grandma?

210
00:10:01,875 --> 00:10:04,458
Uh--wha?

211
00:10:04,541 --> 00:10:05,500
It's for you.

212
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:07,958
I pray your concert
will go well!

213
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:09,625
Thanks, Grandma.

214
00:10:09,708 --> 00:10:11,291
Okay, I gotta go!

215
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:12,833
[NACHI'S GRANDMA]
You be careful, now!

216
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:13,958
[NACHI]
Sure will!

217
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:19,083
[MAID A]
Pardon me, sir,

218
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:22,041
but the young master
has just returned.

219
00:10:22,125 --> 00:10:23,791
[MIKASA'S DAD grunts]

220
00:10:23,875 --> 00:10:25,833
You're really home!

221
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:28,125
It's good to see
your face, Mikoto.

222
00:10:28,208 --> 00:10:29,500
Hurry up! Come in so we...

223
00:10:29,583 --> 00:10:31,125
[MIKASA'S DAD]
That won't be necessary.

224
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:32,000
[MIKOTO, MIKASA gasp]

225
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,000
[MIKOTO]
Dad.

226
00:10:34,416 --> 00:10:35,708
I'll make it clear.

227
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:37,125
Unless you're here
to tell me that you've

228
00:10:37,208 --> 00:10:39,125
given up music altogether,

229
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:42,625
you can leave right now,
and you're no longer my son.

230
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:44,250
Dad! No!

231
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:45,958
Is that all you
have to say to me?

232
00:10:46,041 --> 00:10:47,291
I'm doing you no favors

233
00:10:47,375 --> 00:10:50,125
if I continue to let you
do as you please forever.

234
00:10:50,208 --> 00:10:51,375
Then, I'm sorry.

235
00:10:51,458 --> 00:10:53,041
I have a gig to get to.

236
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:56,416
You'll have to wake up someday.

237
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:57,625
[MIKASA'S DAD]
Stop wasting your time

238
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:59,125
on such meaningless things!

239
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:01,458
[MIKASA gasps] Hope you'll
forgive me for repeating myself,

240
00:11:01,541 --> 00:11:04,541
but what I do has tremendous
meaning, at least for me.

241
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:05,625
Goodbye, Dad.

242
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:06,791
No, wait!

243
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:09,625
If you go now,
he won't let you--[gasps]

244
00:11:09,708 --> 00:11:13,125
Sis, this is the most important
thing in the world to me.

245
00:11:13,208 --> 00:11:14,750
Sorry, I have to go.

246
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:26,375
Okay, well, I guess I'll
drop in a bit later!

247
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,541
And I need to remember
to thank the owner, too.

248
00:11:28,625 --> 00:11:29,583
[SARA]
Cool.

249
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:33,041
[HISA]
Sara!

250
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:34,208
Here it comes.

251
00:11:34,291 --> 00:11:36,625
Go out and show 'em
what you're made of!

252
00:11:36,708 --> 00:11:37,708
Yup.

253
00:11:40,458 --> 00:11:42,083
Ha! This is amazing.

254
00:11:42,166 --> 00:11:43,208
She's never been able to

255
00:11:43,291 --> 00:11:45,291
stick with any band
this long before!

256
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:47,875
I guess she really must
feel at home with them.

257
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:50,791
Either that, or she
actually is growing up.

258
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:52,500
Nah, that can't be it.

259
00:11:52,583 --> 00:11:53,583
--[door opens]
--Huh?

260
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:54,708
Hey, Yassan.

261
00:11:54,791 --> 00:11:55,541
Yo.

262
00:11:55,625 --> 00:11:56,500
What's goin' on?

263
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:57,708
Come with me.

264
00:11:57,791 --> 00:11:59,541
We have surprise visitors.

265
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:01,375
You're not gonna believe it.

266
00:12:03,958 --> 00:12:04,916
[HISA gasps]

267
00:12:07,375 --> 00:12:10,083
Tama... and Nico?

268
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,791
It's been a long time.

269
00:12:12,875 --> 00:12:13,916
Hey, man.

270
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:18,250
[HISA] So, I mean...
when did you guys get back?

271
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,750
[TAMA]
Like, just now.

272
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,750
And where the heck have you
been all this time, anyway?

273
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:24,083
You were gone for
six freakin' years!

274
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:25,125
That's wild.

275
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:26,916
Has it seriously been that long?

276
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,000
Not cool.

277
00:12:28,083 --> 00:12:30,125
You never wrote,
you never called.

278
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:32,000
Sorry about that.

279
00:12:33,166 --> 00:12:36,583
I need to talk to you all about
something, if that's okay.

280
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:38,791
[HISA]
Huh?

281
00:12:58,708 --> 00:13:00,708
[inhales, exhales]

282
00:13:19,208 --> 00:13:20,083
Uh--

283
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,500
There!

284
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:38,208
--[car horn honks]
--[gasps]

285
00:13:43,125 --> 00:13:45,041
[MIKASA gasps]
Oh. Sorry, you guys.

286
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:45,958
I must be late.

287
00:13:46,041 --> 00:13:47,250
[SARA]
Nah, you're not late.

288
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,250
Huh?

289
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:52,625
I guess we were all so anxious
that we got here early.

290
00:13:52,708 --> 00:13:54,833
Now Akitsuki's the
only one missing.

291
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,250
[FUUKA gasps]

292
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:13,208
You wanna die?

293
00:14:13,291 --> 00:14:15,750
No! I'm so sorry, sir!

294
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,125
Be more careful!

295
00:14:43,166 --> 00:14:44,875
[FUUKA]
Sorry I'm late, everybody!

296
00:14:44,958 --> 00:14:46,291
Look who decided to show up!

297
00:14:46,375 --> 00:14:47,375
[YUU]
We were getting worried!

298
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:48,750
Did something happen?

299
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:50,250
Not really!

300
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:51,541
It was nothing.

301
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:59,166
Let's go out there and
be the stuff of legends!

302
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,208
[ALL]
Yeah!

303
00:15:03,041 --> 00:15:04,125
[CROWD cheering]

304
00:15:04,208 --> 00:15:06,000
Hey, we're The Fallen Moon!

305
00:15:06,083 --> 00:15:06,875
Let's do it!

306
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:09,958
[CROWD cheering]

307
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:11,708
You guys might know this one.

308
00:15:11,791 --> 00:15:14,208
Here's "Climber's High"
by the Hedgehogs.

309
00:15:30,083 --> 00:15:31,416
They're covering our stuff?

310
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:32,583
How adorable.

311
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:33,916
[TOMOMI]
Aren't they so great?

312
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,625
Did you know they're
also my students?

313
00:15:35,708 --> 00:15:36,750
That's amazing.

314
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,583
How'd you ever get
a job as a teacher?

315
00:15:38,666 --> 00:15:41,416
Well, I guess you could say that
I've turned over a new leaf!

316
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,000
That leaf's jumpy.
It flips over quite a lot.

317
00:15:44,083 --> 00:15:45,375
Quiet, you!

318
00:15:45,458 --> 00:15:48,041
[FUUKA]
♪ ...done trying to blend in ♪

319
00:15:48,125 --> 00:15:51,666
Wow. Hisashi, isn't
that your sister?

320
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:52,791
[HISA]
Sure is.

321
00:15:52,875 --> 00:15:54,750
She's actually pretty good, man.

322
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:56,708
Yeah, She's not bad.

323
00:15:56,791 --> 00:15:58,791
[FUUKA] ♪ It's hard to change
it up When no one else ♪

324
00:15:58,875 --> 00:16:01,208
♪ is listening
We're in a box, stuck in a box ♪

325
00:16:01,291 --> 00:16:03,708
And this girl, she's good.

326
00:16:03,791 --> 00:16:06,333
[FUUKA] ♪ Forced to erase
all that we know is real ♪

327
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:07,875
♪ But I refuse to be locked up ♪

328
00:16:07,958 --> 00:16:10,708
♪ Won't live in this prison
Gotta fight for open skies ♪

329
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:18,000
--[applause]
--[CROWD cheering]

330
00:16:18,083 --> 00:16:24,041
[music playing]

331
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:45,958
[music continues playing]

332
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:51,250
♪ When I look deep within
There is a town I see ♪

333
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:56,583
♪ It flickers like a flame
That's fading slowly ♪

334
00:16:56,666 --> 00:17:01,958
♪ The things I used to know
The things I once believed ♪

335
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:07,291
♪ Are fading from my mem'ry ♪

336
00:17:07,375 --> 00:17:09,833
♪ Like a shadow in the dark ♪

337
00:17:09,916 --> 00:17:12,625
♪ Something shapeless
and unknown ♪

338
00:17:12,708 --> 00:17:14,000
Are you serious?

339
00:17:14,083 --> 00:17:15,583
'Fraid so.

340
00:17:15,666 --> 00:17:17,250
You're telling me...

341
00:17:17,333 --> 00:17:19,458
...she turned down a
contract with Mogami?

342
00:17:19,541 --> 00:17:21,625
Yep, right there on the spot.

343
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:24,416
Respect. Though it seems
like a wasted shot.

344
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:28,166
But you want them to stay
exactly as they are, don't you?

345
00:17:29,208 --> 00:17:30,333
Yeah, I do.

346
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:32,791
[TAMA chuckles]

347
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:37,083
[gasps] He's on my bass.

348
00:17:37,166 --> 00:17:39,125
How'd that happen?

349
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:40,083
[FUUKA]
♪ Like snowfall... ♪

350
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:42,583
Oh, yeah. I lent it to him.

351
00:17:42,666 --> 00:17:45,083
You left it here to gather
dust for years, anyway.

352
00:17:45,166 --> 00:17:47,333
Well, even if I did,

353
00:17:47,416 --> 00:17:49,875
still wasn't your call.

354
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:52,291
♪ Now I can see ♪

355
00:17:52,375 --> 00:17:55,291
♪ Once again,
that light aflame ♪

356
00:17:55,375 --> 00:18:00,625
♪ A place forgotten
Now remembered for all time ♪

357
00:18:00,708 --> 00:18:03,250
♪ No matter our distance ♪

358
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:06,000
♪ Whatever comes between us ♪

359
00:18:06,083 --> 00:18:08,583
♪ Here in the town
where stars fall ♪

360
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:15,416
♪ Is where I pray I'll be ♪

361
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:17,458
[CROWD cheering]

362
00:18:17,541 --> 00:18:20,541
Thank you so much,
you guys! [laughs]

363
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:23,500
Really.

364
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:26,000
Like I said before, we're called
The Fallen Moon and we

365
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:29,875
appreciate you so much, because
this is only our second show!

366
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:31,791
[CROWD gasps]

367
00:18:31,875 --> 00:18:35,333
So, we--we don't have much of a
set list built up quite yet.

368
00:18:35,416 --> 00:18:38,375
But next, we're gonna play
our new original song!

369
00:18:38,458 --> 00:18:42,875
[CROWD cheering]

370
00:18:42,958 --> 00:18:45,958
[inhales, exhales]

371
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:50,708
So for our last number,
I hope you enjoy.

372
00:18:50,791 --> 00:18:51,750
"For You."

373
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,958
[CROWD cheers]

374
00:19:18,708 --> 00:19:21,041
♪ Oh, I got so much on my mind ♪

375
00:19:21,125 --> 00:19:23,625
♪ Hard for me to keep
looking forward ♪

376
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:26,208
♪ Dragging my feet,
my body's so tired ♪

377
00:19:26,291 --> 00:19:28,958
♪ But still,
I keep on going my way ♪

378
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:31,625
♪ I try to joke
around pretending ♪

379
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:34,083
♪ That it's not over,
but I know ♪

380
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:38,333
♪ I'm searching for an answer
That's unknown ♪

381
00:19:38,416 --> 00:19:41,500
♪ I was just lying to myself ♪

382
00:19:41,583 --> 00:19:44,166
♪ Acting like I have
so much confidence ♪

383
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:48,416
♪ My smile was
nothing but a mask ♪

384
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,875
♪ Don't know if tomorrow
will ever come ♪

385
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:53,958
♪ Or if I'm even meant
to last till dawn ♪

386
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:59,208
♪ So let's get real ♪

387
00:19:59,291 --> 00:20:00,541
♪ Why not let it out? ♪

388
00:20:00,625 --> 00:20:02,708
♪ There's nothing to lose
Go deep in my heart ♪

389
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,541
[KOYUKI]
These lyrics.

390
00:20:04,625 --> 00:20:06,416
[FUUKA]
♪ Singing, singing ♪

391
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:09,500
♪ What I'm feeling for you ♪

392
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:11,875
♪ Hurrying but still
taking my time ♪

393
00:20:11,958 --> 00:20:14,375
♪ And running but standing
still all the while ♪

394
00:20:14,458 --> 00:20:18,000
♪ I'll accept any challenge
If that's what it takes ♪

395
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:19,916
♪ For you to share
your life with me ♪

396
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:25,958
[music playing]

397
00:20:34,541 --> 00:20:36,541
[CROWD cheering]

398
00:20:36,625 --> 00:20:37,916
[MALE FAN A]
Where you gonna play next?

399
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,000
[MALE FAN B]
Come play here again!

400
00:20:47,791 --> 00:20:49,458
[NACHI]
Hey, hey, hey!

401
00:20:49,541 --> 00:20:52,000
We just got invited to
play another show soon!

402
00:20:52,083 --> 00:20:53,125
Seriously?

403
00:20:53,208 --> 00:20:55,083
My brother is gonna
be so thrilled!

404
00:20:55,166 --> 00:20:56,583
How cool!

405
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:58,458
I guess we'd better start
getting ready for it right away!

406
00:20:58,541 --> 00:21:00,416
Yeah, no kidding! Hm?

407
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:04,416
[chuckles] Maybe we should
have the great master, Fuuka,

408
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:07,708
start working on a new original
song for that show, too!

409
00:21:10,291 --> 00:21:12,541
Hey, Akitsuki, what's wrong?

410
00:21:12,625 --> 00:21:14,416
Well...

411
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:15,875
Actually...

412
00:21:15,958 --> 00:21:18,875
There's something I really
need to tell you guys about.

413
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,000
[OTHERS]
Huh?

414
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,791
We're here for you.

415
00:21:25,875 --> 00:21:28,375
The thing is, I've been scouted,

416
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:31,000
so... I'm going to
make my solo debut.

417
00:21:31,083 --> 00:21:31,958
What?

418
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,750
Wait, you mean...

419
00:21:33,833 --> 00:21:37,166
...you're going to leave
The Fallen Moon to go solo?

420
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,291
You have gotta be kidding me.

421
00:21:41,375 --> 00:21:42,625
This is unreal.

422
00:21:42,708 --> 00:21:44,000
We rocked the hell
out of that show

423
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:46,125
and we're only just
getting started!

424
00:21:46,208 --> 00:21:47,458
Why now, Fuuka?

425
00:21:47,541 --> 00:21:50,125
Because, it's my dream.

426
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:51,666
So, you're out?

427
00:21:52,958 --> 00:21:54,375
Are you saying...

428
00:21:54,458 --> 00:21:57,166
...you don't think the band can
make your dream come true?

429
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:59,000
Yeah, I guess so.

430
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:02,958
And your mind's made up?

431
00:22:03,041 --> 00:22:04,291
[FUUKA]
Mm-hmm.

432
00:22:04,375 --> 00:22:05,541
[groans]

433
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:08,500
I see.

434
00:22:08,583 --> 00:22:11,250
I think one thing is
pretty clear here.

435
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,000
The band cannot
survive without you.

436
00:22:13,083 --> 00:22:14,375
[NACHI]
Right?

437
00:22:14,458 --> 00:22:16,291
Even so, there's
no chance I would

438
00:22:16,375 --> 00:22:19,041
stand in the way of you
pursuing your dream.

439
00:22:19,125 --> 00:22:21,125
[NACHI]
You're not just gonna accept it?

440
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:22,625
What choice do we have?

441
00:22:22,708 --> 00:22:25,375
And what about you? You agree?

442
00:22:25,458 --> 00:22:27,250
If that's what
Fuuka wants to do.

443
00:22:27,333 --> 00:22:30,291
[NACHI groans]
Damn it!

444
00:22:30,375 --> 00:22:32,541
Haruna, c'mon! Say something!

445
00:22:32,625 --> 00:22:33,708
[YUU gasps]

446
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:39,041
I've gotta take a
step toward my dream.

447
00:22:39,125 --> 00:22:40,625
I'm sorry, guys.

448
00:22:42,375 --> 00:22:47,333
♪

449
00:22:54,041 --> 00:22:56,666
<i>Looking up at the sky</i>
<i>I felt an emptiness</i>

450
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:59,583
<i>All the colors of</i>
<i>summer have been faded</i>

451
00:22:59,666 --> 00:23:03,166
<i>Before I even knew the things</i>
<i>that made me the happiest</i>

452
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:05,166
<i>Were hidden and tucked away</i>

453
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:08,000
<i>But when I looked at you</i>
<i>it all felt so intense</i>

454
00:23:08,083 --> 00:23:10,875
<i>Your eyes cut to the</i>
<i>core of my existence</i>

455
00:23:10,958 --> 00:23:14,333
<i>Every word that you spoke</i>
<i>was like a painting in every hue</i>

456
00:23:14,416 --> 00:23:16,166
<i>You brought calm into my world</i>

457
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:18,708
<i>All I can do now is breathe</i>

458
00:23:18,791 --> 00:23:21,666
<i>And figure out just what I need</i>

459
00:23:21,750 --> 00:23:24,291
<i>Resolve myself, pursue my dreams</i>

460
00:23:24,375 --> 00:23:26,833
<i>I'm running</i>

461
00:23:26,916 --> 00:23:29,625
<i>Moving forward, taking your hand</i>

462
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:31,000
<i>Being with you</i>

463
00:23:31,083 --> 00:23:32,666
<i>I'm finally free enough to</i>
<i>spread out my wings</i>

464
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:35,166
<i>Let's catch the wind</i>
<i>and go for a ride</i>

465
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:39,083
<i>You and I can fly</i>
<i>anywhere together</i>

466
00:23:39,166 --> 00:23:41,500
<i>We can go as high</i>
<i>up as we want</i>

467
00:23:41,583 --> 00:23:44,291
<i>Following the path that's</i>
<i>been laid pout before us</i>

468
00:23:44,375 --> 00:23:47,875
<i>Guided by our</i>
<i>bonded hearts forever</i>

469
00:23:47,958 --> 00:23:51,291
<i>Let's keep living</i>
<i>out this fantasy</i>

470
00:23:51,375 --> 00:23:55,291
<i>And chasing our dreams</i>

471
00:23:55,375 --> 00:23:58,625
<i>Ah... Ah...</i>

472
00:23:58,708 --> 00:24:03,666
♪

473
00:24:13,458 --> 00:24:15,333
[FUUKA]
Next time, "Band."

